In determining the amount of the penalty, the Commissioner or the administrative law judge shall consider:
the gravity of the violation;
the size of the employer's business;
the employer's good faith;
the employer's history of violations under this subtitle; and
whether the employer:
has been found, by a court or an administrative unit, to have deprived the employee of any rights to which the employee would have been entitled under a State protective labor law, including but not limited to:
has made restitution and come into compliance with all such State protective labor laws with respect to the employee.
